South African-born Master KG has people around the globe dancing to his hit track 'Jerusalema'. Twitter/@MasterKGsa JOHANNESBURG - There is clearly no stopping Jerusalema hitmaker, Master KG, as he bags yet another accolade. The artist announced on Twitter that he has won the best international song at the NRJ Music Awards. READ: Master KG scoops MTV EMA award  The awards are presented by a French radio station to honour musicians across the globe. The Jerusalema Youtube video has been viewed more than 2-million times, and people worldwide have taken part in the Jerusalema dance challenge. READ: SA lauds 'Jerusalema' producer for MTV Best African Act Master KG beat out artists such as Nicky Minaj, Jason Derulo & Dua Lupa in winning the award.